author: dlr
msg: On Bay's agreement, removed the implode/explode class methods.  The
more Perl-like names seem more descriptive of the type of processing
occurring in the methods.  Bay indicates the the implode/explode names
had their roots in LPC (a C-like object language).

author: dlr
msg: Merged explode() methods into split() (now slightly more efficent for
lesser parameter versions).  Added new split(String) overload.

author: dlr
msg: Added test for new split() method.

author: dlr
msg: Added blub about what types of code the Util project is for.
